# Cursor Rules for AI Quiz Answering App

## Project Patterns

### File Naming
- Screenshot files follow macOS pattern: "Screenshot YYYY-MM-DD at HH.MM.SS"
- Python files use snake_case
- Template files use kebab-case

### Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 guidelines
- Use type hints where possible
- Document all functions with docstrings
- Keep functions focused and small

### Project Structure
- Keep main logic in app.py
- CLI interface in cli.py
- Templates in templates/
- Documentation in memory-bank/
- Configuration in .env

### Development Workflow
- Test changes locally first
- Update documentation with changes
- Keep memory bank in sync
- Monitor performance impacts

## User Preferences
- Prefer Conda for environment management
- Use VSCode/Cursor for development
- Keep UI simple and clean
- Maintain clear error messages

## Known Challenges
- Screenshot timing sensitivity
- API rate limiting
- Memory management for history
- UI update latency

## Best Practices
- Always validate API key presence
- Clean up processed screenshots
- Handle network errors gracefully
- Provide clear user feedback

## Tool Usage
- Use watchdog for file monitoring
- Flask for web interface
- Pillow for image handling
- python-dotenv for configuration

## Project Intelligence
- Critical paths require error handling
- UI updates should be non-blocking
- Keep processing pipeline efficient
- Maintain clear status indicators 